- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for approximating random variables.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of a random variable with respect to a distance metric, which is a common problem in machine learning.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with discrete random variables and their approximation.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper presents a formal analysis of the computational complexity of the algorithm.
